WEBVTT

00:00.006 --> 00:01.792
<i>Previously on "Imposters"...</i>

00:01.862 --> 00:03.128
Seattle.

00:03.163 --> 00:05.296
- She's in Seattle.
- Seattle?

00:07.601 --> 00:08.933
He's an assignment, sweetie pie.

00:10.227 --> 00:12.561
<i>Patrick Campbell could be
one of our biggest scores.</i>

00:12.846 --> 00:14.880
The numbers aren't good.
They are amazing.

00:14.915 --> 00:16.148
Not in a million years, Max.

00:16.183 --> 00:18.150
Oh, yes, you most definitely will.

00:18.185 --> 00:19.885
The payoff is huge.

00:19.920 --> 00:20.886
What's the payoff?

00:20.921 --> 00:22.287
We get to live.

00:22.322 --> 00:24.122
<i>If you ever go to the police</i>

00:24.158 --> 00:26.491
<i>or try to find me, everyone in the world</i>

00:26.527 --> 00:28.927
<i>will know what's inside that folder.</i>

00:28.962 --> 00:30.295
I bet whatever's in your folder

00:30.330 --> 00:31.547
is way worse than what's in mine.

00:31.547 --> 00:33.465
I have literally no idea
what you're talking about.

00:33.500 --> 00:34.536
Yeah, me neither.

00:35.769 --> 00:37.169
Ready to go?

00:37.204 --> 00:38.503
We were never going to run.

00:38.539 --> 00:41.173
You need to stop saying "we."

00:41.208 --> 00:42.974
Rules of the game, Sal.

00:43.010 --> 00:44.643
- You broke 'em.
- Maxie.

00:44.678 --> 00:46.111
<i>This is your ex-wife.</i>

00:46.146 --> 00:47.479
<i>Your shape-shifting, money-stealing,</i>

00:47.514 --> 00:49.481
<i>professional con artist ex-wife,</i>

00:49.516 --> 00:51.349
<i>and mine, and his.</i>

00:51.385 --> 00:53.652
Guys, we need a Maddie code.

00:53.687 --> 00:54.753
No alone time.

00:54.788 --> 00:56.755
No contacting her on our own.

00:56.790 --> 00:58.957
No sex.

00:58.992 --> 01:01.960
I'm gonna throw you one
kick-ass birthday party.

01:01.995 --> 01:04.782
I hate birthday parties, always have.

01:04.816 --> 01:05.831
Until you met me.

01:08.067 --> 01:09.229
Ez.

01:11.344 --> 01:13.271
- Hi, Ava.
- What are you...

01:15.098 --> 01:16.608
- Alice.
- How did you...

01:16.643 --> 01:19.311
Hey, Ce.

01:19.346 --> 01:20.846
What the f...?

01:22.000 --> 01:28.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:36.096 --> 01:37.529
- Excuse me.
- Whoa, whoa,

01:37.564 --> 01:38.830
what are you doing?

01:38.866 --> 01:41.099
Going to the bathroom. Is that okay?

01:44.838 --> 01:46.838
May I please use the restroom?

01:46.874 --> 01:48.173
You're not really in a position

01:48.208 --> 01:49.690
to take that tone...

01:51.411 --> 01:53.311
- But yes.
- Come right back.

01:53.347 --> 01:55.580
And no funny business.

02:04.291 --> 02:05.991
Jesus Christ.

02:06.026 --> 02:08.326
Okay, we're okay. It's okay.

02:08.362 --> 02:11.162
Oh, my God, she looks so different,

02:11.198 --> 02:12.898
but I can see Alice in there.

02:12.933 --> 02:14.432
I see Cece.

02:14.468 --> 02:17.369
I see something,
but I don't think it's Ava.

02:19.273 --> 02:21.439
Does anybody else feel like puking?

02:50.404 --> 02:53.638
Well, here I am.

02:56.147 --> 02:58.209
Now what?

03:08.368 --> 03:11.034
Fine, I'll start.
You found me, congratulations.

03:11.069 --> 03:12.270
That's right. We did.

03:12.305 --> 03:14.372
Yeah, and we're not leaving
until we get what we came for.

03:14.407 --> 03:16.407
What'd you come for?

03:16.443 --> 03:17.942
Don't you wanna know how we found you?

03:17.978 --> 03:19.611
Why don't you just
tell me what you want?

03:19.646 --> 03:21.346
- You stole our money.
- Yeah, that's right.

03:21.381 --> 03:23.181
You can't just take people's money.

03:23.216 --> 03:24.349
You didn't just steal our money.

03:24.384 --> 03:26.284
You took... our dignity.

03:26.319 --> 03:28.553
Wrong. No one can take that from you

03:28.588 --> 03:31.222
unless you give it to them.

03:31.258 --> 03:32.957
Anything else?

03:32.993 --> 03:34.392
Yeah, you at least owe us some answers.

03:34.427 --> 03:36.027
I don't have any answers.

03:36.062 --> 03:37.562
Well, you haven't heard
the questions yet.

03:37.597 --> 03:38.897
Let me guess.

03:38.932 --> 03:41.466
How could I do this to you? Right?

03:41.501 --> 03:44.269
- Or better yet, "Why me?"
- Yeah, exactly, why us?

03:44.304 --> 03:45.870
Because it's my job.

03:45.906 --> 03:47.405
It's what I do.

03:47.440 --> 03:49.574
And because you let me.

03:51.132 --> 03:52.000
Um...

03:52.312 --> 03:54.579
Okay, we're willing to cut you a deal.

03:54.614 --> 03:56.414
- A deal.
- Mm-hmm.

03:56.449 --> 04:01.786
There's no deal to be made
because there is no money.

04:01.821 --> 04:04.289
Uh, what about everything
you stole from us?

04:04.324 --> 04:05.823
It's gone.

04:05.859 --> 04:07.959
- It's gone?
- Yep.

04:07.994 --> 04:09.294
What, it's just gone?

04:09.329 --> 04:11.763
- That's right.
- Okay, bullshit.

04:11.798 --> 04:13.598
We're entitled to the truth.

04:13.633 --> 04:15.166
- You want the truth?
- Yeah.

04:15.201 --> 04:17.334
And we're not leaving until we get it.

04:20.005 --> 04:21.539
Okay.

04:21.574 --> 04:23.908
Here's your truth.

04:23.944 --> 04:29.013
You are in way,
way over your heads, okay?

04:29.049 --> 04:31.582
If I screw up this job
that I'm doing right now,

04:31.618 --> 04:36.087
if you screw it up for me,
then he is going to kill me.

04:36.122 --> 04:40.959
He's going to kill me in a very slow,
painful way.

04:40.994 --> 04:42.327
Who are you talking about?

04:42.362 --> 04:45.196
What, you think I do
what I do all by myself?

04:47.500 --> 04:50.835
All right, so,
here's what's gonna happen.

04:50.870 --> 04:53.338
I'm going to get up,
and I'm gonna walk out that door,

04:53.373 --> 04:55.640
and then each of you
are going to turn around

04:55.675 --> 04:59.243
and go back to your lives
because if you don't,

04:59.279 --> 05:02.146
then I'm quite literally a dead person.

05:02.182 --> 05:06.451
And then all of you are not far behind.

05:06.486 --> 05:08.818
There's your truth.

05:09.689 --> 05:12.490
What just happened?

05:12.525 --> 05:14.826
- Ava... get out, let me out!
- What are you...

05:14.861 --> 05:16.639
Maddie, wait!

05:17.931 --> 05:20.131
- Oh, God.
- Okay, he'll get her.

05:20.166 --> 05:21.933
He'll bring her.

05:21.968 --> 05:24.235
- Maddie!
- I don't feel so good.

05:24.270 --> 05:25.741
Oh, God.

05:27.807 --> 05:29.440
Thank you.

05:31.277 --> 05:32.610
- Are they ready for us?
- Uh, I think so.

05:32.645 --> 05:34.645
- We just head right over here.
- Okay.

05:37.784 --> 05:41.452
How many weeks in Seattle,
and you've already got an admirer.

05:41.488 --> 05:43.435
Nicely done.

05:45.458 --> 05:46.791
Huh.

05:46.826 --> 05:48.426
What's the matter? Wrong guy?

05:48.461 --> 05:52.096
No, no, if anything, he's too right.

05:52.132 --> 05:53.531
It's me.

05:53.566 --> 05:55.600
Well, either call
that gentleman and tell him

05:55.635 --> 05:57.301
you'd like to thank him in the flesh

05:57.337 --> 05:59.504
or give me his number.

06:07.213 --> 06:09.013
Jesus Christ.

06:09.049 --> 06:11.015
How soon can we get out
of this goddamn bank?

06:11.051 --> 06:13.158
Whoa. Whoa, hold on.

06:13.158 --> 06:14.754
Look, Max.

06:16.322 --> 06:19.057
This morning at the diner...

06:22.328 --> 06:24.996
I just... I can't...
I can't work here anymore, okay?

06:25.031 --> 06:27.865
I thought after Heller was,
you know, gone

06:27.901 --> 06:29.000
that they'd let me go.

06:29.035 --> 06:31.969
I mean, couldn't I just quit?

06:32.005 --> 06:36.207
No, no, no, you gotta keep on
like nothing's changed.

06:36.242 --> 06:38.009
- You want some advice?
- What?

06:38.044 --> 06:39.377
You wanna quit being a secretary?

06:39.412 --> 06:41.212
Make yourself a wife ASAP.

06:41.247 --> 06:44.515
I mean, it looks like
you're on your way, right?

06:44.551 --> 06:45.650
Just doing my job.

06:45.685 --> 06:47.485
Good, that's good to hear.

06:48.588 --> 06:50.088
Toaster pastry?

06:52.392 --> 06:53.691
I don't buy it, guys.

06:53.726 --> 06:55.026
I mean, who would want to kill her?

06:55.061 --> 06:56.794
Besides us?

06:56.830 --> 06:59.063
Maybe it's like she said.
She's accountable to someone.

06:59.099 --> 07:02.300
I mean, what we need to know
is does she have a new mark.

07:02.335 --> 07:04.035
I mean, is she already married?

07:04.070 --> 07:05.937
Was she wearing a ring?

07:05.972 --> 07:08.239
Oh, I didn't even notice.

07:08.274 --> 07:09.841
Oh, me neither.

07:09.876 --> 07:11.709
Shit, guys,
this isn't amateur hour, okay?

07:11.744 --> 07:13.211
We gotta get it together.

07:13.246 --> 07:15.012
By doing what, exactly? She's a liar.

07:15.048 --> 07:16.347
We have zero information.

07:16.382 --> 07:18.549
She just played us and left again.

07:18.585 --> 07:20.051
I mean, how is it possible
she doesn't have

07:20.086 --> 07:21.085
any of our money?

07:21.121 --> 07:22.520
I need that money, all right?

07:22.555 --> 07:23.721
If I don't get that money, I'm screwed.

07:23.756 --> 07:25.389
Okay, okay, you're right.

07:25.425 --> 07:27.091
We don't know what
we're dealing with here.

07:27.127 --> 07:29.594
And we can't know what
to do until we find out,

07:29.629 --> 07:32.763
so let's get to work.

07:39.072 --> 07:41.405
You having a tough day?

07:44.310 --> 07:48.813
Sorry, everything at the bank.
My boss and...

07:48.848 --> 07:50.748
It's just so sudden, so strange.

07:50.783 --> 07:52.216
No, don't apologize.

07:52.252 --> 07:55.786
You don't need to be
any certain way with me.

07:55.822 --> 07:58.089
Just be you.

08:00.026 --> 08:03.060
You are just so sweet. You know that?

08:04.531 --> 08:05.763
Yeah, you got it!

08:05.798 --> 08:06.931
Just want me to wait or just go?

08:06.966 --> 08:08.666
So fake, aw.

08:08.701 --> 08:10.823
Ugh, fake, fake-ity fake, fake.

08:10.858 --> 08:12.236
Yeah, man, that's so fake.

08:12.272 --> 08:13.337
Looks pretty real to me.

08:13.373 --> 08:14.805
I'm not believing it.

08:14.841 --> 08:17.141
Poor schmuck. He's totally doomed,

08:17.177 --> 08:18.609
and he doesn't even know it.

08:18.645 --> 08:19.777
I don't think he's struggled much.

08:19.812 --> 08:21.078
He's gonna be fine.

08:21.114 --> 08:22.747
- Have a heart, dude.
- Heart-schmart.

08:22.782 --> 08:24.415
We want our money back? There you go.

08:24.450 --> 08:26.083
This guy's a juicy target.

08:26.119 --> 08:27.985
Well, gotta hand it to her,
at least she's

08:28.021 --> 08:29.921
gone back to my type.

08:29.956 --> 08:33.424
I mean, he's good-looking,
well-built, charismatic.

08:33.458 --> 08:34.659
Look at that smile.

08:34.693 --> 08:36.994
Well, maybe you should date him.

08:37.030 --> 08:39.496
Uh, hold up, it looks like
we got a bogey at 3:00.

08:39.532 --> 08:43.201
- "Bogey," isn't that golf?
- No, I mean in a "Top Gun" way.

08:44.537 --> 08:46.108
Who do you think this is?

08:48.341 --> 08:49.540
I don't know.

08:49.576 --> 08:52.343
- Sister, maybe?
- Racist.

08:52.378 --> 08:53.811
It was the way they're saying hi!

08:53.846 --> 08:56.347
Guys, shh!

08:56.382 --> 08:57.782
Racist.

08:57.817 --> 09:00.384
Man, she's meeting his family already.

09:00.420 --> 09:03.054
It's not that I don't
like birthday parties.

09:03.089 --> 09:06.157
It's just that I don't like
being the center of attention.

09:06.192 --> 09:08.059
Oh, you think the party is about you?

09:08.094 --> 09:10.361
Oh, no, no, no, no,
he just wants to show off

09:10.396 --> 09:11.696
what a great boyfriend he is.

09:11.731 --> 09:13.297
Hey, hey!

09:13.333 --> 09:15.866
Well, I mean, yeah, but still.

09:15.902 --> 09:17.235
Doughnut, is that a doughnut?

09:17.270 --> 09:18.803
I love those kind of doughnuts, man.

09:18.838 --> 09:20.171
Dude, how do we not have
any snacks, man?

09:20.206 --> 09:21.472
- Dude.
- All good stakeouts

09:21.507 --> 09:23.074
- have snacks.
- We've been here

09:23.109 --> 09:24.508
- like five minutes.
- Oh, target's on the move.

09:24.544 --> 09:25.509
- They're getting up.
- Uh-oh.

09:25.545 --> 09:26.877
- Okay.
- What do we do?

09:26.913 --> 09:28.913
Uh, don't know.

09:28.948 --> 09:30.581
Uh-oh, looks like
they're splitting up, guys.

09:30.617 --> 09:31.916
- What's the plan?
- Okay, three of them,

09:31.951 --> 09:34.106
three of us. I say we split up too.

09:34.282 --> 09:35.119
I call Alice!

10:07.300 --> 10:09.718
_

10:13.170 --> 10:15.257
_

10:28.998 --> 10:30.731
Can I help you find something?

10:30.767 --> 10:32.867
Yeah, you know, I don't...
I don't know a whole lot

10:32.902 --> 10:34.935
about flowers,
but I'm trying to convince

10:34.971 --> 10:37.905
my new sort-of-girlfriend
that I do by buying

10:37.940 --> 10:40.040
a lot of flowers for her birthday.

10:42.376 --> 10:46.549
_

10:50.853 --> 10:52.753
- Hey.
- Oh, my God, how are you?

10:52.789 --> 10:54.588
- Hi. I'm good. And you?
- It's good to see you.

10:54.624 --> 10:56.390
- Yeah, good, I'm just...
- Yeah, what's up?

10:56.425 --> 10:58.626
It's Patrick's girlfriend's birthday.

10:58.661 --> 11:00.225
_

11:00.325 --> 11:02.630
_

11:08.703 --> 11:11.202
_

11:13.376 --> 11:15.276
- I'm on it.
- Thank you.

11:19.048 --> 11:20.915
Are you Patrick?

11:22.351 --> 11:23.350
Yeah.

11:23.386 --> 11:24.785
Man, I thought it was you.

11:24.821 --> 11:26.921
Wow, this is the craziest coincidence.

11:26.956 --> 11:28.856
<i>This is not gonna be
a repeat of the diner.</i>

11:28.891 --> 11:30.925
<i>Remember, she has
more to lose than we do.</i>

11:30.960 --> 11:33.194
<i>We came here for our money,
and we're gonna get our money.</i>

11:33.229 --> 11:34.995
<i>And we're all gonna
abide by the Maddie code?</i>

11:35.031 --> 11:36.664
<i>- Absolutely
- For sure.</i>

11:36.699 --> 11:38.599
<i>- Let's do this.
- So now we're musketeers?</i>

11:38.634 --> 11:40.267
<i>Come on, guys, don't leave me hanging.</i>

11:40.303 --> 11:42.102
<i>- Always forward.
- Never back.</i>

11:42.138 --> 11:43.195
<i>Sweet.</i>

11:44.073 --> 11:45.139
<i>Yo, handsome.</i>

11:45.174 --> 11:46.173
<i>Yes, beautiful?</i>

11:47.312 --> 11:48.108
Do you mind?

11:48.144 --> 11:51.278
Oh, I don't mind at all. Okay.

11:52.748 --> 11:55.349
Hey, wrong direction.

11:55.384 --> 11:56.417
Well, I mean, we have time, don't we?

11:56.452 --> 11:59.086
Mmm.

11:59.829 --> 12:02.089
I suppose so.

12:03.835 --> 12:05.468
Oh, my goodness.

12:05.504 --> 12:07.037
Who's here so early?

12:07.592 --> 12:08.872
Caterers, probably.

12:08.907 --> 12:11.157
Always messing up my plans.

12:12.111 --> 12:13.878
Hold that thought.

12:20.353 --> 12:21.852
- Hey!
- Hello!

12:21.888 --> 12:24.054
- Good to meet you.
- Yeah, nice to meet you.

12:24.090 --> 12:26.657
This is my girlfriend.
Happy to meet you too.

12:28.527 --> 12:30.928
Hey, come on down.
I got a little surprise for you.

12:30.963 --> 12:32.494
Patrick.

12:34.867 --> 12:36.667
What did I say?

12:36.702 --> 12:39.036
- We talked about this.
- I know.

12:39.071 --> 12:41.272
I told you, no surprises.

12:41.307 --> 12:43.173
You're gonna really
like this one, though.

12:43.209 --> 12:44.868
Surprise!

12:46.812 --> 12:48.545
Oh, my God!

12:48.581 --> 12:51.215
I cannot believe my baby
sister is turning 30.

12:51.250 --> 12:52.716
What happened?

12:53.541 --> 12:54.885
I don't know.

12:54.921 --> 12:57.054
I mean, I didn't even know
you had a brother,

12:57.089 --> 12:58.956
and then this guy shows
up at the flower stand,

12:58.991 --> 13:01.191
and he's calling out my name.
It was incredible.

13:01.227 --> 13:03.527
That is incredible.

13:03.562 --> 13:06.063
- Wow, how did you, um...
- Well, you told me

13:06.098 --> 13:09.033
all about your new mystery man,
sent me all those cute photos.

13:09.068 --> 13:10.634
So when I saw him,
I had to say something.

13:10.670 --> 13:13.404
I mean, have you ever
fallen for a guy so fast?

13:13.439 --> 13:15.706
- Ezra, you're embarrassing me.
- What?

13:15.741 --> 13:17.408
No, don't stop, though,
'cause I'm loving it.

13:18.489 --> 13:19.310
Oh, God, I'm so sorry.

13:19.345 --> 13:21.211
This is my girlfriend, Jules.

13:21.247 --> 13:24.281
Jules, meet my sister, Saffron.
She's 30 today.

13:24.317 --> 13:26.216
- So I hear.
- Wow.

13:26.252 --> 13:28.452
It's so lovely to meet you finally.

13:28.487 --> 13:30.621
Nice to meet you too.

13:30.656 --> 13:32.456
Okay. Stop it.

13:32.491 --> 13:34.491
Wow, so many people
that love you in one room.

13:34.527 --> 13:36.660
This is gonna be a fantastic party.

13:36.696 --> 13:39.730
Yeah, did anyone offer anyone a drink?

13:39.765 --> 13:41.065
I was just headed there.

13:41.100 --> 13:42.599
Come on, follow me, guys.

13:44.303 --> 13:45.970
What can I get you guys?

13:46.005 --> 13:47.404
Birthday girl first.

13:47.440 --> 13:51.008
Oh, birthday girl? Wow, happy birthday.

13:51.043 --> 13:52.776
What's your poison?

13:52.812 --> 13:54.011
Something strong.

13:54.046 --> 13:55.512
- One for me too.
- And me.

13:55.548 --> 13:58.148
All right,
how about a cocktail I invented?

13:58.184 --> 14:01.819
Clean, classy,
disappears without a trace.

14:01.854 --> 14:03.354
Call it the "Alice."

14:04.390 --> 14:07.324
That sounds wonderful.

14:07.360 --> 14:09.664
- Four Alices.
- All right.

14:14.533 --> 14:16.000
Yeah, it's just so pretty.

14:16.035 --> 14:20.304
Come on, Max, answer your phone.

14:20.339 --> 14:21.839
<i>You've reached my cell. Leave a message.</i>

14:21.874 --> 14:24.008
Shit.

14:29.882 --> 14:31.615
Yeah, it's only been two weeks.

14:31.650 --> 14:33.050
- Really?
- Yeah.

14:33.085 --> 14:35.352
That's hilarious
I did not know that, wow.

14:35.388 --> 14:37.621
So you live right here in Seattle?

14:37.656 --> 14:39.023
Well, Bellevue.

14:39.058 --> 14:40.624
Suburbs, you know, they get a bad rap,

14:40.659 --> 14:43.027
but, uh, what can I say?
I like being able to park.

14:43.062 --> 14:44.294
Yeah, I understand that.

14:44.330 --> 14:45.562
Oh, excuse me.

14:45.598 --> 14:47.431
Oh, no problem.

14:51.537 --> 14:53.337
Having fun?

14:53.372 --> 14:54.335
Yeah.

14:55.107 --> 14:57.238
I sure didn't expect all of this.

14:57.943 --> 14:59.309
But you know Patrick.

14:59.345 --> 15:01.378
He loves bringing people together.

15:01.414 --> 15:02.646
Mm-hmm.

15:02.681 --> 15:03.981
You know, Patrick never mentioned

15:04.016 --> 15:05.682
that you had a brother.

15:05.718 --> 15:10.421
Mm, yeah, well, I think family
is the most important thing,

15:10.456 --> 15:12.222
- don't you?
- Oh, I do.

15:12.258 --> 15:14.725
You really get to know
someone when you finally

15:14.760 --> 15:16.927
- meet their family.
- And big brothers are the best.

15:16.962 --> 15:19.229
- Ahh.
- You have any other siblings...

15:19.265 --> 15:21.999
No, no, just the one. Excuse me.

15:22.034 --> 15:24.501
So finally, finally,
I'm like, yes, okay, fine,

15:24.537 --> 15:26.103
you can cut my hair, and she cuts

15:26.138 --> 15:28.939
an enormous bald spot
in the back of my head.

15:28.974 --> 15:30.674
And then I'm like, okay,
I'm gonna do the same thing

15:30.709 --> 15:33.177
to your dolls,
and I was the one that got in trouble

15:33.212 --> 15:35.746
because Saffron, I don't know, man,

15:35.781 --> 15:37.848
she always knew how to
manipulate our mom and dad.

15:37.883 --> 15:41.351
It's like she has this whole
shape-shifting thing going on.

15:43.122 --> 15:45.122
Is my brother being a
pain in the ass again?

15:45.157 --> 15:46.857
No, no, he's a funny guy.

15:46.892 --> 15:48.092
You know, it's nice to hear some things

15:48.127 --> 15:49.693
about your childhood.

15:49.728 --> 15:51.095
She tells me so little,
I was starting to think

15:51.130 --> 15:52.696
she was raised in a cult.

15:52.731 --> 15:54.398
Well, a cult would've been
a lot more interesting

15:54.433 --> 15:55.632
than Pottsville.

15:55.668 --> 15:57.434
Pottsville? Where's that?

15:57.470 --> 15:59.403
Pottsville, Pennsylvania, hometown.

15:59.438 --> 16:01.071
Wait, I... I thought Cincinnati?

16:01.107 --> 16:02.639
It's Cincinnati.

16:02.675 --> 16:04.475
Right, we're originally
from Cincinnati...

16:04.510 --> 16:05.943
- Right.
- But our uncle got sick,

16:05.978 --> 16:07.277
and we moved to Pottsville.

16:07.313 --> 16:08.879
- Uncle Sam.
- And let me tell you,

16:08.914 --> 16:10.647
Pottsville had never seen
anything like Saffron.

16:10.683 --> 16:12.249
Stop.

16:12.284 --> 16:13.984
When's...
when's the last time you visited?

16:14.019 --> 16:15.719
- Ezra.
- No, no, no, it's fine.

16:15.754 --> 16:17.754
You know, things are a bit
tough back there, you know.

16:17.790 --> 16:21.458
Our dad, his, uh... his memory's
going down, you know, and, uh...

16:21.494 --> 16:24.261
But this one, she's still
the apple of his eye, huh?

16:24.296 --> 16:25.996
Anyway, sorry, not tonight.

16:26.031 --> 16:27.831
Patrick, where are...
where are you from?

16:27.867 --> 16:30.267
Uh, Chicago, originally, then...

16:30.302 --> 16:31.335
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

16:31.370 --> 16:32.613
You're welcome.

16:34.507 --> 16:36.140
How come he's getting
all the play with her

16:36.175 --> 16:37.474
and I'm stuck here like a dishrag?

16:37.510 --> 16:38.775
They're not alone.

16:38.811 --> 16:40.944
Technically not a code violation.

16:40.980 --> 16:44.281
- Well, I still don't like it.
- Hey, how was your little chat?

16:44.316 --> 16:46.316
One-on-ones are not cool, remember?

16:46.352 --> 16:48.452
And that wasn't a one-on-one,
and your breath smells

16:48.487 --> 16:49.753
