you to go that far to find me.

22:24.745 --> 22:26.269
Maybe you underestimated me.

22:27.266 --> 22:28.899
Maybe.

22:35.408 --> 22:40.344
- You seem different, Ezra.
- Yeah?

22:40.379 --> 22:44.048
I still see you in there.

22:44.083 --> 22:47.317
You see... Ava?

22:47.353 --> 22:48.986
I see Maddie.

22:52.892 --> 22:56.260
I see you too.

22:56.295 --> 22:58.429
- Really?
- Yep.

22:58.464 --> 23:00.264
Always could,

23:00.299 --> 23:04.701
see you, be with you, so easily.

23:08.874 --> 23:13.177
Ooh-ho-ho, wow. I remember that look.

23:13.212 --> 23:14.578
What look?

23:14.613 --> 23:16.113
The, uh, "this is something special,

23:16.148 --> 23:18.248
you're the only one who gets me" look.

23:18.284 --> 23:21.452
- Mm.
- How do you do that?

23:21.487 --> 23:25.189
You just throw your heart
around like it's nothing.

23:25.224 --> 23:28.592
I don't know.
Maybe it's different this time.

23:28.627 --> 23:30.594
Maybe he's not just a mark.

23:33.666 --> 23:37.634
If that's what you need
to tell yourself, then... great.

23:37.670 --> 23:39.970
- You guys do look alike.
- Mm-hmm.

23:40.005 --> 23:42.272
I mean, coloring and all. It's crazy.

23:42.308 --> 23:44.241
There's some crucial differences.

23:44.276 --> 23:47.778
- There are.
- I hope so.

23:47.813 --> 23:50.447
All right, she's all yours, man.

23:50.483 --> 23:52.316
Enjoy yourself.

23:55.988 --> 23:57.221
Don't start.

23:57.256 --> 23:58.956
Okay, definite code violations.

23:58.991 --> 24:00.724
One-on-one, touching, out of control.

24:00.759 --> 24:03.427
- That wasn't a one-on-one...
- Shh.

24:06.799 --> 24:10.534
- You got anything with Amarula?
- How about Amarula?

24:10.569 --> 24:13.437
I'll take some Amarula.

24:13.472 --> 24:15.572
- Glass of Amarula.
- Mm-hmm.

24:15.608 --> 24:17.107
- Pretty awesome.
- Yeah?

24:17.143 --> 24:19.343
- Yeah.
- What are you drinking?

24:19.378 --> 24:20.978
