don't really think my art

31:53.478 --> 31:56.779
"marries the playful
subversivism of Duchamp

31:56.814 --> 32:00.917
with the sublime sensuality of Kahlo"?

32:00.952 --> 32:02.318
How drunk is she?

32:02.353 --> 32:04.220
Not... not enough.

32:04.255 --> 32:08.157
Sit down, everyone. Now.

32:12.797 --> 32:14.230
Do you know why you're here?

32:14.265 --> 32:16.599
We're not here for any trouble, okay?

32:16.634 --> 32:18.768
- We just want our money.
- Wrong.

32:18.803 --> 32:21.504
You came here to chase a phantom.

32:21.539 --> 32:23.306
People do crazy things for love.
I get it.

32:23.341 --> 32:25.975
If they didn't, well,
I wouldn't be in business.

32:26.010 --> 32:28.744
But know this: there's no Ava;

32:28.780 --> 32:30.846
there's no Cece; there's no Alice;

32:30.882 --> 32:34.483
and there's no money, not now, not ever.

32:34.519 --> 32:36.819
Says you.

32:36.854 --> 32:38.287
I'm sorry?

32:38.323 --> 32:40.189
"A," you're a con artist,
so what you say

32:40.224 --> 32:43.526
doesn't exactly hold water.
"B," we can blow the lid

32:43.561 --> 32:45.328
off this whole thing
in five seconds flat...

32:45.363 --> 32:46.662
- Yeah.
- If you don't guarantee us

32:46.698 --> 32:48.531
- a piece of the action.
- True that.

32:48.566 --> 32:50.499
- "A piece of the action."
- Mm-hmm.

32:50.535 --> 32:52.635
At what price, hmm?

32:52.670 --> 32:54.270
Are you willing to destroy your mother

32:54.305 --> 32:56.005
and bring down Bloom Boot & Heel

32:56.040 --> 32:58.674
in one fell swoop when I reveal to Mumsy

32:58.710 --> 33:00.810
that your father has a
sweet little side dish

33:00.845 --> 33:03.279
named Chanterelle and that the entire

33:03.314 --> 33:05.982
family business is built
upon a stolen patent?

33:06.017 --> 33:07.683
Whoa, seriously?

33:07.719 --> 33:10.186
And are you going to be
able to live with yourself

33:10.221 --> 33:12.655
when your hometown finds out
that you threw that interception

33:12.690 --> 33:18.060
on purpose to beat the spread?
And for what, 10 grand?

33:18.096 --> 33:19.128
That's pretty weak.

33:19.163 --> 33:20.363
That money went to my mom.

33:20.398 --> 33:21.664
- Nobody cares, son.
- I knew it.

33:21.699 --> 33:24.000
I knew you guys had your own secrets.

33:24.035 --> 33:25.468
So it seems we're all con artists

33:25.503 --> 33:27.970
in our own way, aren't we?

33:28.006 --> 33:31.657
- And poor Jules...
- Do not go there.

33:33.511 --> 33:36.512
Please don't forget that
we have this information.

33:36.547 --> 33:39.315
Leave town today, or we'll use it.

33:39.350 --> 33:41.817
And my last and most important point:

33:41.853 --> 33:44.654
if anything interferes
with Maddie doing this job,

33:44.689 --> 33:47.757
the people who sent her
here to do this job,

33:47.792 --> 33:49.225
well, simply put,

33:49.260 --> 33:51.560
they will kill her, they will kill me,

33:51.596 --> 33:53.362
and, as far as you three bumblers go...

33:53.398 --> 33:56.332
Hey, man, don't threaten us.
I'm telling you...

33:56.367 --> 33:57.333
- Oh!
- Whoa!

34:00.538 --> 34:02.338
And, oh, yeah, there's that.

34:02.373 --> 34:05.174
Don't let me see any of you ever again.

34:24.795 --> 34:26.529
Josh, what is it?

34:26.563 --> 34:28.597
Why have you been calling
for the last three hours?

34:28.632 --> 34:30.599
<i>Jesus, Ezra, why haven't you
been answering your phone?</i>

34:30.635 --> 34:32.201
<i>Dad had a heart attack.</i>

34:32.235 --> 34:33.436
What?

34:33.471 --> 34:35.271
I-Is he okay?

34:35.306 --> 34:36.605
<i>We don't... We don't know, man.</i>

34:36.641 --> 34:38.139
<i>You just... You need to come home.</i>

34:38.176 --> 34:40.543
<i>Mom is... It's rough here, man.</i>

34:40.578 --> 34:42.509
<i>Just get home now.</i>

34:47.618 --> 34:49.652
What's going on, man?

34:52.023 --> 34:53.589
What?

35:09.307 --> 35:11.440
You have the post-party blues?

35:11.476 --> 35:13.776
Mm, no.

35:13.811 --> 35:18.514
Just, you know, a year older.

35:18.549 --> 35:20.116
I don't think I'm any wiser.

35:20.151 --> 35:24.954
Mm, I think you're a lot
wiser than you know.

35:24.989 --> 35:27.857
Thank you.

35:27.892 --> 35:30.159
Really, thank you

35:30.194 --> 35:32.628
for the party,

35:32.663 --> 35:37.166
the fireworks, everything.

35:37.201 --> 35:38.968
You're amazing.

35:39.003 --> 35:41.137
And I'm not even done yet.

35:41.172 --> 35:42.671
I mean, you didn't think
I was gonna really let

35:42.707 --> 35:43.939
your birthday pass without giving you

35:43.975 --> 35:46.609
an actual gift, did you?

35:46.644 --> 35:48.344
- Patrick.
- Hold on. Give me one second.

35:48.379 --> 35:50.679
- We... ugh.
- One second.

35:50.715 --> 35:54.450
I would like you to open this,

35:54.485 --> 35:55.684
please, madam.

35:55.720 --> 36:00.289
Oh, my God, you have done enough.

36:09.567 --> 36:12.334
Worth way more than anything
I have to put in it.

36:12.370 --> 36:15.070
Oh, then we gotta do
something about that.

36:15.106 --> 36:16.705
And you should probably leave some room

36:16.741 --> 36:19.508
for a little vacation
shopping when you pack.

36:19.544 --> 36:21.010
When I pack?

36:21.045 --> 36:23.345
Yeah, I thought this weekend,
I'd take you

36:23.381 --> 36:25.481
for a little getaway, unless, of course,

36:25.516 --> 36:26.734
you don't wanna go.

36:28.686 --> 36:30.419
Wait, wait, don't you even
wanna know where we're going?

36:30.454 --> 36:33.656
No, no, no, anywhere
that's away with you

36:33.691 --> 36:37.059
is exactly where I wanna be.

36:50.074 --> 36:51.841
How long you gonna go for?

36:51.876 --> 36:54.009
I'll know more when I get there, uh...

36:59.984 --> 37:04.553
Hey, I'm so sorry about your dad.

37:04.589 --> 37:06.689
But you know this isn't over.

37:06.724 --> 37:09.358
Oh, maybe, or maybe
we just have to accept

37:09.393 --> 37:11.694
that we're not getting
what we came here to get.

37:11.729 --> 37:13.696
We don't even know what
we came here to get,

37:13.731 --> 37:17.900
so there's no reason to think
we can't still get it, right?

37:17.935 --> 37:20.269
You know, what's scary
is that I'm starting

37:20.304 --> 37:22.137
to understand your logic.

37:24.075 --> 37:25.274
I think you miss me already.

37:25.309 --> 37:27.209
Yeah, yeah, uh, in your dreams.

37:43.594 --> 37:44.960
Take care of yourself, all right?

37:44.996 --> 37:46.996
- Yeah, okay.
- Talk to you soon.

38:03.547 --> 38:06.615
Let me just say again,
I really, really, really

38:06.651 --> 38:08.617
think it's a stupid idea.

38:08.653 --> 38:10.352
You need the electrolytes. Drink up.

38:10.388 --> 38:13.022
No, just... will you just
listen to me for a second?

38:13.057 --> 38:15.624
Max said that Cece
was in actual trouble,

38:15.660 --> 38:18.193
like violence, death.

38:18.772 --> 38:19.628
He's a con artist.

38:19.664 --> 38:20.663
He was lying.

38:20.698 --> 38:21.931
What if he wasn't?

38:21.966 --> 38:23.432
Look, she chose this life, all right?

38:23.467 --> 38:24.800
Patrick didn't.

38:24.835 --> 38:26.535
- He's a good guy.
- He's fine.

38:26.570 --> 38:28.671
- Whatever, it doesn't...
- Let me ask you something.

38:28.706 --> 38:31.140
What if somebody could've
come to you after you met Cece

38:31.175 --> 38:32.841
but before she totally
screwed up your life

38:32.877 --> 38:36.879
and could've done something,
could've stopped it, huh?

38:39.417 --> 38:41.517
Just, what if someone tries to hurt her?

38:42.264 --> 38:43.252
Or us?

38:43.287 --> 38:45.454
I mean, I really think you
should call Ezra before you...

38:45.489 --> 38:47.022
I don't need Ezra's permission, okay?

38:47.058 --> 38:48.357
I'm going.

38:48.392 --> 38:49.959
You can stay here,
or you can come with me.

38:49.994 --> 38:51.460
- Ugh, you can't leave.
- All right, watch me.

38:51.495 --> 38:53.228
- We're a team or whatever.
- All right?

38:53.264 --> 38:55.364
- Always forward, never back.
- That doesn't even apply

38:55.399 --> 38:56.966
in this case if you... Wait, Richie!

38:58.520 --> 38:59.735
You'll ruin everything.

39:19.751 --> 39:21.751
Oh, shit.

39:56.321 --> 39:58.988
Ah, shit, come on.

40:07.098 --> 40:08.531
Patrick!

40:14.706 --> 40:16.013
God damn it.

40:16.875 --> 40:17.822
Ahh.

40:19.219 --> 40:21.377
Patrick!

40:21.412 --> 40:24.013
Oh, ahh.

40:27.252 --> 40:28.451
No, come on.

40:32.757 --> 40:33.956
Excuse me.

40:33.992 --> 40:35.458
Patrick!

40:38.555 --> 40:39.295
Next.

40:42.267 --> 40:44.066
Okay, just put it in there.

40:44.102 --> 40:46.102
- Thank you.
- You can go through.

40:55.613 --> 40:57.113
Hey.

40:58.683 --> 41:00.049
Thanks.

41:01.653 --> 41:03.019
Can I help you?

41:03.054 --> 41:05.355
Uh, yeah, man, I'm just looking for...

41:08.093 --> 41:09.726
What's up, superstar?

41:09.761 --> 41:11.194
Thank you. Good morning.

41:12.897 --> 41:15.198
That's right, late.

41:15.233 --> 41:16.966
Late.

